steps.userPrompt:
Fetch full details and description entries for each discovered incident:

{{discover-incidents.output}}

For each incident in the 'incidents' array:
1. Get the full incident details
2. Get the description entries (comments)

Output a single JSON object:
{
  "<incident_id>": {
    "incident": { ...full incident details... },
    "descriptions": [ ...description entries... ]
  }
}

Return ONLY the JSON content, nothing else.

Check the investigation state for each discovered incident.

Discovered incidents:
{{discover-incidents.output}}

For each incident:
1. Use Zakira.Exchange get_memory with the incident ID as key
2. Apply the decision logic from your instructions

Output a JSON object:
{
  "incidentsToInvestigate": [
    {
      "incidentId": "<id>",
      "reason": "never-investigated|stale-investigation|failed-retry",
      "existingState": null | { "status": "...", "startedAt": "...", ... },
      "incidentTitle": "<title>",
      "severity": <severity number>
    }
  ],
  "incidentsSkipped": [
    {
      "incidentId": "<id>",
      "reason": "already-completed" | "investigation-in-progress",
      "incidentTitle": "<title>"
    }
  ]
}

If incidentsToInvestigate is empty, call orchestra_complete. Otherwise output the JSON.
